==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plausibility
<hw>Plau`si*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>plausibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something worthy
of praise.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Integrity, fidelity, and other gracious
<qex>plausibilities</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>E. Vaughan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being plausible;
speciousness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To give any <qex>plausibility</qex> to a scheme.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything plausible or specious.</def> <rj><au>R.
Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plausible</ent>⟦br⟧
